ork and in modernism generallyAppears at a time when Eliot has been, and will continue to be, much in the news and closely studied because of the publication of his letters, collected poems and proseHailing from the UK, US, Continental Europe and India, the contributors to this volume have recently published significant books on modernism and the arts, shaping the fields that they here develop with respect to Eliot Interart studies is a new and rapidly growing field, particularly in music and dance"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEliot, T.SxCriticism and interpretation. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh1 aAllen, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoyle, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuda, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDickey, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFaulk, Barry J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraham, T. Austin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHargrove, Nancy D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHobbs, Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMabie, Joshua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorgenstern, John D., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMorgenstern, John D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaterson, Adrian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSarkar, Malobika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchuchard, Ronald, econ